These are accessibility pitfalls.

00:16:24.900 --> 00:16:28.420
Usually, these items
within page builders are not accessible,

00:16:28.620 --> 00:16:31.420
so we need to keep
a very close eye on them,

00:16:31.620 --> 00:16:34.900
and in some cases,
we'll avoid them completely.

00:16:35.500 --> 00:16:36.700
Don't worry, though.

00:16:36.940 --> 00:16:44.060
I'll offer some good, more accessible
alternatives to those items as well.

00:16:45.420 --> 00:16:52.660
Bringing us in strong, waving us in
with that red flag are interactive elements.

00:16:52.820 --> 00:16:57.980
These are items such as flip boxes,
interactive circles, flip carousels.

00:16:58.140 --> 00:17:00.980
I mean, honestly, anything that says flip

00:17:01.060 --> 00:17:03.980
or interactive within
a page builder, I just say-

00:17:04.100 --> 00:17:05.460
[chuckles] I usually nope out of.

00:17:05.660 --> 00:17:13.580
These kinds of items like
to take valuable content and hide them

00:17:13.700 --> 00:17:17.620
from the user or force them
to interact with it

00:17:17.740 --> 00:17:19.500
in order to be able to see it.

00:17:19.660 --> 00:17:24.340
This could be in the form
of a hover or a focus

00:17:24.500 --> 00:17:28.700
that the user has to perform
in order to see this content

00:17:28.860 --> 00:17:32.180
because it's hidden behind
a box or an element.

00:17:32.380 --> 00:17:39.060
These are definitely
an avoid completely in my list.

00:17:39.220 --> 00:17:44.020
They are excluding users,
and they're just plain bad.

